  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Promoting rights and supporting emergency protection needs in MMC, Jere and Monguno, Borno State</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">As an early responder to the influx of IDPs into Monguno town and the Maiduguri metropolitan area (including both MMC and Jere LGAs), the IRC has seen first-hand the acute and often life-threatening protection concerns faced by those displaced from their homes and livelihoods by the conflict. The displaced population is varied in demographics (men, women, boys and girls) as well as protection needs. As a result, the IRC is proposing a comprehensive and community-based approach to addressing acute protection needs including support for Unaccompanied and Separated Children (UASC), case management and access to assistance for victims of gender based violence (GBV) and sexual exploitation and abuse (SEA) to ensure that displaced communities maintain dignity and are able to hold government and community authorities accountable. The IRC&#x2019;s proposed 5-month intervention will draw on expertise from the protection sector including GBV and child protection subsectors. 
Project activities will reach an estimated 50,745 persons, but the exact number cannot yet be targeted due to the very fluid situation</narrative>
  </description>
